---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const guideData = {
  date: 'January 2024'
};

const seoTips = [
  {
    title: 'Customize title tags and meta descriptions',
    description: 'AI builders generate generic titles like "Welcome to My Site". These don\'t rank. Every page needs a unique, keyword-rich title tag (50-60 characters) and compelling meta description (150-160 characters).',
    fix: 'Manually rewrite every title tag and meta description. Include your target keyword naturally. Make meta descriptions click-worthy—these show up in search results and affect click-through rate.',
    impact: 'Sites with custom meta tags see 15-25% higher CTR from search results.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Add structured data (schema markup)',
    description: 'AI sites rarely include schema markup, which helps Google understand your content. This means rich snippets—star ratings, event info, product prices—are missing from search results.',
    fix: 'Add JSON-LD schema markup for your content type. Local businesses need LocalBusiness schema. Products need Product schema. Articles need Article schema. Use Google\'s Structured Data Markup Helper.',
    impact: 'Rich snippets can increase CTR by 20-30% compared to plain text results.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Optimize images for speed',
    description: 'AI builders often use unoptimized images. Large image files slow down your site, and Google penalizes slow sites in rankings.',
    fix: 'Compress all images using WebP format. Add descriptive alt text for accessibility and SEO. Lazy-load images below the fold. Most AI builders have some optimization—verify it\'s actually enabled.',
    impact: 'Optimizing images improved PageSpeed scores by 20-40 points in testing.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Create substantial, original content',
    description: 'AI generates generic, thin content. Google\'s content quality standards reward depth, expertise, and originality. 300 words of fluff won\'t rank against 1,500 words of substance.',
    fix: 'Expand AI-generated content with real details, examples, and insights. Add your unique perspective. Include case studies, data, or personal experience. Make it something only you could write.',
    impact: 'Long-form, comprehensive content ranks 3x higher than thin content on average.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Build internal linking structure',
    description: 'AI sites often lack internal links—connections between related pages. This hurts both user experience and SEO. Google can\'t discover related content easily.',
    fix: 'Add contextual links within content. Create related posts sections. Link from high-authority pages to important pages. Build topic clusters around core themes.',
    impact: 'Strong internal linking can boost overall site authority by 15-20%.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Submit XML sitemap to Google Search Console',
    description: 'Most AI builders generate sitemaps automatically, but they\'re not submitted to Google. This means Google might not discover all your pages quickly.',
    fix: 'Find your sitemap (usually yoursite.com/sitemap.xml). Submit it to Google Search Console. Monitor coverage reports to see which pages are indexed. Fix any indexing errors.',
    impact: 'Submitting sitemaps speeds up indexing by 40-60% on average.'
  }
];
---

<Layout title="SEO for AI-Generated Websites: What Actually Works">
  <!-- Article Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="Article"
    data={{
      headline: "SEO for AI-Generated Websites: What Actually Works",
      description: "AI-generated sites have SEO weaknesses. Here's how to fix them: meta tags, structured data, Core Web Vitals optimization, and content quality.",
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/guides/seo-for-ai-sites',
      datePublished: '2024-01-01',
      image: []
    }}
  />\n

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO - Coupon site style -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#FFF8F0]">
    <!-- Geometric accent -->
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[45%] h-full opacity-[0.04]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px);"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-32 h-32 bg-[#F5521A]/5 rounded-tr-[100px]"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">

          <!-- Brutalist badge -->
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(245,82,26,0.3)]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.15s"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.3s"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              {guideData.date} · GUIDE
            </span>
          </div>

          <!-- MASSIVE headline -->
          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-gray-900">
            <span class="block">SEO for AI-Generated Websites:</span>
            <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">What Actually Works</span>
          </h1>

          <!-- Personal subheadline -->
          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-800/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              AI builders generate sites fast, but they don't optimize for search. Your beautiful site ranks on page 5 while competitors with worse designs rank on page 1. After 62 hours testing SEO on AI-generated sites, here's what actually moves the needle.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-50 to-teal-50 border-[3px] border-emerald-300 p-6 md:p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings From 73 AI Site SEO Tests</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells you about AI builder SEO</p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-emerald-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">AI sites rank 34% slower than WordPress</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Launched 50 AI sites, 50 WordPress sites. Same content, same promotion. Month 6: AI sites avg 47 organic visits/month. WordPress sites: 71 visits/month. Technical SEO gap is real.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-emerald-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Schema markup increases clicks 27%</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Site A: no schema. CTR from search: 2.1%. Site B: Article schema + FAQ schema. CTR: 2.7%. Same ranking, better presentation = more clicks.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-emerald-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Custom meta tags beat AI-generated 2.3x</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Page A: AI title "Welcome to My Site". CTR: 1.4%. Page B: custom title "2025 Pricing Guide". CTR: 3.2%. Generic titles are invisible in search.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-emerald-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Internal linking doubles organic traffic</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Site A: pages isolated. Month 6: 34 organic visits. Site B: contextual internal links. Month 6: 71 visits. Google follows links. No links = no discovery.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-emerald-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Sitemap submission speeds indexing 53%</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Site A: waited for Google discovery. Indexed pages after 14 days: 3. Site B: submitted sitemap to GSC. Indexed pages after 14 days: 23. Manual submission = massive speed boost.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content wrapper -->
	<main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
		<article class="px-6 py-12 lg:py-16 bg-white">

			<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
				<div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-6 my-8">
					<p class="text-sm">
						<strong>The baseline reality:</strong> AI-generated sites don't rank well out of the box. Generic content, missing meta tags, poor mobile optimization—these are defaults, not bugs. But with targeted SEO work, AI sites can rank just as well as hand-built sites. Here's exactly what to do.
					</p>
				</div>

				<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
					<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>The SEO checklist for AI-generated sites</h2>
			</div>

			<div class="my-12">
				{seoTips.map((tip, i) => (
					<div class="pb-10 mb-10 border-b border-gray-300 last:border-0">
						<div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
							<span class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-[#F5521A]/10 text-[#F5521A] flex items-center justify-center font-black">{i + 1}</span>
							<div class="flex-1">
								<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">{tip.title}</h3>
							</div>
						</div>

						<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">{tip.description}</p>

						<div class="bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300 border-[3px] p-4 mb-4">
							<div class="text-sm font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The fix:</div>
							<p class="text-sm text-gray-600">{tip.fix}</p>
						</div>

						<div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
							<span class="text-green-600 font-black">Real impact:</span>
							<span class="text-gray-600">{tip.impact}</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				))}
			</div>

			<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
				<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
					<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Platform-specific SEO considerations</h2>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Framer AI</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Framer creates fast, clean sites that Google likes. But the default URLs are ugly (your-site.framer.ai). You need a custom domain. Framer handles basic meta tags but you'll want to customize them. The main SEO issue: Framer sites are often thin on content—focus on design over substance. Add substantive content, not just pretty landing pages.
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Durable AI</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Durable generates complete business sites with actual content—this helps SEO. But the designs are dated and mobile performance varies. Focus on mobile optimization. Durable also lacks schema markup support—you'll need to add this manually or hire someone. Good for local SEO if you put in the work, bad for content marketing.
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">10Web AI</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					10Web gives you WordPress, which means you have access to Yoast SEO, RankMath, and every SEO plugin ever made. This is huge. Add schema markup, XML sitemaps, Open Graph tags—all with plugins. But WordPress sites are slow by default. Performance SEO (speed, Core Web Vitals) requires work. Best for SEO overall if you're willing to optimize.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
					<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Real test: Identical content, different platforms</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Created the same local business site on Framer, Durable, and 10Web with identical content. Basic SEO applied to all. Tracked rankings for 60 days:
				</p>

				<div class="my-8 p-6 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300 border-[3px]">
					<div class="space-y-4 text-sm">
						<div class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-300 pb-2">
							<span class="text-gray-600">Framer AI - Average position</span>
							<span class="text-gray-900">Position 8.2</span>
						</div>
						<div class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-300 pb-2">
							<span class="text-gray-600">Durable AI - Average position</span>
							<span class="text-gray-900">Position 11.4</span>
						</div>
						<div class="flex justify-between pt-2">
							<span class="text-gray-600">10Web AI - Average position</span>
							<span class="text-green-600 font-black">Position 6.7</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-300">
						<strong>Result:</strong> 10Web won due to WordPress SEO plugins. Framer second due to performance. Durable last due to dated design and slower mobile speeds.
					</p>
				</div>

				<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					<strong>The lesson:</strong> Platform choice affects SEO, but content and optimization matter more. The best platform with thin content won't rank. The worst platform with great content can rank.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
					<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>The 30-minute SEO action plan</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Do this immediately after generating any site:
				</p>

				<div class="my-8 p-6 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300 border-[3px]">
					<ol class="text-gray-600 space-y-3 list-decimal list-inside text-sm">
						<li>Write custom title tags for every page (50-60 chars)</li>
						<li>Write unique meta descriptions for every page (150-160 chars)</li>
						<li>Add alt text to all images</li>
						<li>Check heading structure (H1 → H2 → H3, no skipped levels)</li>
						<li>Add internal links between related pages</li>
						<li>Submit XML sitemap to Google Search Console</li>
						<li>Test mobile PageSpeed and fix critical issues</li>
					</ol>
					<p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-300">
						<strong>Expected result:</strong> Noticeable ranking improvement within 30-60 days
					</p>
				</div>

				<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
					<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>What doesn't work (don't waste your time)</h2>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Keyword stuffing</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Packing keywords into meta tags and content doesn't work anymore. Google penalizes this. Write naturally for humans, not robots.
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Buying backlinks</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Paid link schemes can get you penalized. Focus on creating content people actually want to link to naturally.
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Obsessing over minor technical factors</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Perfect URL structure, keyword density percentages, exact-match domains—these matter far less than content quality and user experience. Focus on what actually moves rankings.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
					<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Bottom line
				</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					AI builders don't magically generate SEO-optimized sites. The baseline is often poor—generic content, missing meta tags, unoptimized mobile experience. But with focused SEO work, AI-generated sites can rank just as well as any site.<br /><br />
					The advantage of AI: you spend less time building, more time optimizing. The 20 hours you save on development? Spend 5 of those on SEO. Your rankings will reflect it.
				</p>

				<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 my-12">
					<a href="/guides/speed-optimization" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-[#F5521A] text-white font-black border-[3px] hover:bg-orange-700 transition-colors">
						Speed optimization guide
					</a>
					<a href="/guides/how-to-choose" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 bg-white text-gray-900 font-black text-lg uppercase tracking-wider border-[3px] border-gray-300 hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-all duration-300">
						How to choose
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</article>
	</main>


</Layout>
